Egis Falls for Second Day on Profit Drop, Prospect of Extra Cost

-- B y   K r y s t o f   C h a m o n i k o l a s
-- 
2011-08-10T09:02:17Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-10/egis-falls-for-second-day-on-profit-drop-prospect-of-extra-cost.html
Egis Nyrt., an Hungarian drugmaker,
fell for a second day, to its lowest in more than two years,
after saying its second-quarter profit shrank 45 percent and it
expects its annual costs to rise by 5 billion forint ($26
million).  The company, owned by Laboratoires Servier, tumbled as much
as 5.4 percent to 16,000 forint, its lowest intraday level since
June 2009, and traded down 2.7 percent at 16,450 forint as of
10:55 a.m. in Budapest.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Krystof Chamonikolas in Prague at 
 kchamonikola@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Gavin Serkin at   gserkin@bloomberg.net  